1
00:00:05,790 --> 00:00:11,366
Māyā, we are told, she’s ashamed
sometimes to come before Kṛṣṇa

2
00:00:11,366 --> 00:00:16,826
because she has this task
of deluding the jīvas.

3
00:00:16,956 --> 00:00:19,919
[Maya Works for Krishna]

4
00:00:19,919 --> 00:00:24,158
But that is our choice—
reign in hell [or] serve in heaven.

5
00:00:24,158 --> 00:00:27,231
So, for those 
who opt to reign in hell,

6
00:00:27,231 --> 00:00:32,437
which is the deluded position
for the eternal servitor of Kṛṣṇa,

7
00:00:32,437 --> 00:00:37,988
then they need to forget
their servitor identity,

8
00:00:37,988 --> 00:00:46,580
and voyeuristically envision 
themselves as lords, masters.

9
00:00:46,580 --> 00:00:54,991
So, there is an interesting verse 
in the 7th chapter of the Bhagavad-gītā:

10
00:00:54,991 --> 00:01:00,090
daivī hy eṣā guṇa-mayī
mama māyā duratyayā

11
00:01:00,090 --> 00:01:04,520
mām eva ye prapadyante
māyām etāṁ taranti te 
[Bg: 7.14]

12
00:01:04,520 --> 00:01:08,671
So Kṛṣṇa says,
“That Māyā, who’s deluding you,

13
00:01:08,671 --> 00:01:11,673
who’s, like, impossible
to overcome—

14
00:01:11,673 --> 00:01:16,340
mama māyā—
she works for Me.

15
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:22,229
So, on your own
you’ll never be able to overcome her,

16
00:01:22,229 --> 00:01:24,722
to defeat her.”

17
00:01:24,722 --> 00:01:28,078
She has some 
infinite backing.

18
00:01:28,078 --> 00:01:31,381
Sometimes Prabhupād would say,
“We should always remember
 

19
00:01:31,381 --> 00:01:37,477
that we are very small,
and Māyā is very great. Don’t …”

20
00:01:37,477 --> 00:01:42,251
He was cautioning us 
against becoming arrogant

21
00:01:42,251 --> 00:01:45,464
and how counter–productive 
that would be

22
00:01:45,464 --> 00:01:46,599
in the spiritual life.

23
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:50,873
Saying, “Māyā is great,
she is working for Kṛṣṇa,

24
00:01:50,873 --> 00:01:53,790
this is her service to Kṛṣṇa.”

25
00:01:53,790 --> 00:01:56,891
Śiva also complains 
of his service,

26
00:01:56,891 --> 00:02:02,655
māyāvādam asac-chāstraṁ 
pracchannaṁ bauddham ucyate

27
00:02:02,655 --> 00:02:08,535
mayaiva kalpitaṁ devi
kalau brāhmaṇa-rūpiṇā
[Pp: 25.7]

28
00:02:08,535 --> 00:02:11,566
“In the kali-yuga I take 
the form of a brāhman,

29
00:02:11,566 --> 00:02:14,255
and I preach māyāvād.”

30
00:02:14,255 --> 00:02:16,151
And Guru Mahārāj says in one place,
he [Śiva] said to Kṛṣṇa,

31
00:02:16,151 --> 00:02:20,946
“Why do I have to do this? 
Make people inimical to You

32
00:02:20,946 --> 00:02:25,339
or forgetful of You,
or to deny Your personality.”

33
00:02:25,339 --> 00:02:29,797
But it’s to facilitate
the free will of the jīvas

34
00:02:29,797 --> 00:02:37,076
and all the spectral range
of its expression.

35
00:02:37,076 --> 00:02:39,243
So, but in this śloka 
says,

36
00:02:39,243 --> 00:02:44,286
daivī hy eṣā guṇa-mayī
mama māyā duratyayā.

37
00:02:44,286 --> 00:02:45,966
“So, what is the solution?

38
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:50,928
Mām eva ye prapadyante—
if you surrender to Me,

39
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:53,208
māyām etāṁ taranti te—
 

40
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:57,116
then you can cross 
beyond the influence of Māyā.

41
00:02:57,116 --> 00:02:59,707
And only that way.

42
00:02:59,707 --> 00:03:05,129
I can withdraw her influence
over you.”

43
00:03:05,129 --> 00:03:07,898
karmāṇi nirdahati kintu ca bhakti-bhājām
[Bs: 5.54]

44
00:03:07,898 --> 00:03:09,978
It’s all in the Brahma-saṁhitā.

45
00:03:09,978 --> 00:03:14,462
When someone comes in connection
with Guru–Gaurāṅga, Rādhā–Govinda,

46
00:03:14,462 --> 00:03:19,352
they are no longer 
under the normal laws of karma,

47
00:03:19,352 --> 00:03:23,046
they come under 
a different jurisdiction

48
00:03:23,046 --> 00:03:26,883
because they’re leaving 
the out-carrying current

49
00:03:26,883 --> 00:03:30,660
that’s going away from the central 
conception of the Absolute

50
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:32,937
and entering the in-carrying current,
 

51
00:03:32,937 --> 00:03:36,741
which is going towards the central 
conception of the Absolute,

52
00:03:36,741 --> 00:03:38,941
in the service.

53
00:03:38,941 --> 00:03:50,603
So, but Māyā is there 
to draw contrast

54
00:03:50,603 --> 00:03:54,123
between the mundane 
and the spiritual,

55
00:03:54,123 --> 00:03:57,958
the formal and the substantial,

56
00:03:57,958 --> 00:04:01,643
fictitious and real devotion—
many things.

57
00:04:01,643 --> 00:04:07,248
So it’s necessary,
just like in a class,

58
00:04:07,248 --> 00:04:12,863
sometimes the teacher
puts a wrong example

59
00:04:12,863 --> 00:04:17,157
and sees if the students
can detect it.

60
00:04:17,157 --> 00:04:19,492
That’s also a type of learning.

61
00:04:19,892 --> 00:04:26,433
But Māyā’s serving indirectly
because in that sense

62
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:32,745
for want of the sufferings 
of material existence

63
00:04:32,745 --> 00:04:39,918
there is a lack of impetus
to take spiritual life seriously.

64
00:04:39,918 --> 00:04:41,883
It’s in the 7th chapter 
of Bhagavad-gītā:

65
00:04:41,883 --> 00:04:46,327
catur-vidhā bhajante māṁ
janāḥ su-kṛtino ’rjuna
[Bg: 7.16]

66
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,898
when Kṛṣṇa says,
“There are four types of people

67
00:04:48,898 --> 00:04:52,935
take spiritual life 
seriuosly:

68
00:04:52,935 --> 00:04:56,025
the distressed—those 
in economic distress;

69
00:04:56,025 --> 00:05:00,679
those who are just stressed;

70
00:05:00,679 --> 00:05:03,679
the jijñāsā—inquisitive;

71
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:08,380
the jñāni—the people who’re really
trying to mind spiritual knowledge.”

72
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:12,038
They’ll be inclined 
towards this.

73
00:05:13,061 --> 00:05:16,581
But so there needs 
to be some impetus.

74
00:05:16,581 --> 00:05:22,177
So, in that way 
Māyā is serving Kṛṣṇa

75
00:05:22,177 --> 00:05:27,485
and serving us
by giving us impetus

76
00:05:27,485 --> 00:05:30,621
to approach the lotus feet 
of guru and Gaurāṅga,

77
00:05:30,626 --> 00:05:33,678
take shelter of sādhu, śāstra, 
guru, Vaiṣṇav.

78
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:35,799
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

